
== CONFIG/ad ==

This is where to place your custom airport data files, named after their
respective ICAO codes with a ".dat" extension. They should follow the X-plane
APT format.

Source files for airports can be found on the X-plane gateway, directly
accessible from the system menu. Extract the "apt.dat" file contained in any
downloaded archive and place it here, renaming it to the right location code.

Alternatively, you may touch up the default data for an airfield yourself, e.g.
to update a single radio frequency or parking position label. To do this, after
a first session has been opened at that location, look for the automatically
generated ".extract" file of the right ICAO code in the "OUTPUT" directory. This
file can be edited and saved here, with its extension changed to ".dat".

